<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 01 at 4:35PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Richmond County through 500 PM EDT...
At 433 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles northwest of Hoffman, or 14 miles north of Rockingham,
this storm is nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Heavy rain is expected with this storm.
Locations impacted include...
Hoffman, Ellerbe, Norman, Sandhills Game Land and Derby.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
